Class PublicKeyObject

All Implemented Interfaces:
NDNContentHandler
public class PublicKeyObject
extends NDNNetworkObject<PublicKey>

A NDNNetworkObject subclass specialized for reading and writing PublicKeys. PublicKeys are Serializable. So we could use a subclass of NDNSerializableObject to serialize them to NDN. But, we want to control their on-the-wire data format -- using their serialization interface, the output will contain metadata only readable via the Java serialization interface. We want to write raw encoded keys. So have to override the serialization behavior. This class also serves as an example of how to write a NDNNetworkObject subclass that needs to implement its own serialization.
